WEBVTT

00:00.500 --> 00:02.000
<font color="#ffff00" size=14>www.tvsubtitles.net</font>

00:01.527 --> 00:05.596
Tonight, Richard and James
enjoy life under canvas.

00:05.596 --> 00:09.867
An Alfa Romeo
waving its arms around.

00:09.867 --> 00:13.951
And Darth Vader
in a Honda Civic TIE fighter R!

00:17.167 --> 00:22.327
Good evening. Back in the late '60s,
Nissan, or Datsun as they were then,

00:22.327 --> 00:27.097
decided to make a sports car.
This is it, the 240Z.

00:27.097 --> 00:31.867
It was a simple recipe. Three parts
E-type Jaguar, two parts Corvette,

00:31.867 --> 00:36.607
and a sprinkling of Japanese
reliability. Fabulous car.

00:36.607 --> 00:42.127
But they kept changing it, and each
time they did, they made it worse.

00:42.127 --> 00:45.807
There was the 260Z, which was plump,

00:45.807 --> 00:49.887
the 280Z, which was...John Prescott,

00:49.887 --> 00:55.607
and finally they ended up with
this enormous thing, the 300ZX.

00:55.607 --> 01:00.707
Marlon Brando, really.
AS BRANDO:. "The horror. The horror. "

01:00.707 --> 01:05.547
We've been joined by some people
from the Nissan Z Club, yes? Yes.

01:05.547 --> 01:08.607
Which is yours? The 280.

01:08.607 --> 01:13.624
What in the name of all that's holy
possessed you to buy that?

01:13.625 --> 01:20.105
I bought it 15 years ago,
and it looked good then.
It's beige with red seats!

01:20.105 --> 01:24.885
Are you from Birmingham? Yes, how
did you guess? That explains it all!

01:24.885 --> 01:30.695
Have you got one? Yes. And you've
got a beard. And you have a beard.

01:30.695 --> 01:34.045
That explains the appeal
of the Z car!

01:34.045 --> 01:39.365
Happily, however, Nissan has now
gone back to basics with the 350Z.

01:39.365 --> 01:44.105
I was so keen to try it out that
when it first arrived in Britain,

01:44.105 --> 01:47.450
I grabbed the keys
and went for a drive.

